<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="25" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="25">
Named after the host genus on which it was collected, 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Meliaceae" genus="Melia" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Melia" order="Sapindales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Melia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="25" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Conidiomata</emphasis>
pycnidial, immersed in the host bark, scattered, erumpent through the bark surface, discoid, with a single locule. 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Ectostromatic disc</emphasis>
dark brown, one ostiole per disc, (325-)330-375(-385) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
(n = 30) diam. 
<taxonomicName genus="Locule" lsidName="Locule" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Locule</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
undivided, 420-640 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
385-515 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
(n = 30). 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Conidiophores</emphasis>
reduced to conidiogenous cells. 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Conidiogenous cells</emphasis>
(13.5-)15-26.5(-28) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.3-2.1(-2.3) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
(n = 30), L/W = 8.5-15.5, cylindrical, hyaline, branched, straight or slightly curved, tapering towards the apex. 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Alpha conidia</emphasis>
hyaline, aseptate, fusiform, multi-guttulate, (6.7-)8-9.5(-10) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
(2-)2.1-2.3 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
(n = 30), L/W = 3.4-4.5. 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Beta conidia</emphasis>
not observed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="25" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Culture characters.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Colony originally flat with white felty aerial mycelium, becoming auburn furcate mycelium with age, with irregular margin, conidiomata absent.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
